rComments: Easy course. Prof did a great job keeping things moving given the size of the class. This course should come earlier in the degree. Lots of interesting stuff that I wish I had known when I started art school, rather than at the end! He has a weird sense of humour, but at least he is not as boring as some of the other profs!

Weird course, interesting professor. I wish the department would have had us take this prior to our final year. Daniel was fascinating and very capable in explaining the very boring parts (documentation etc) of being a professional artist. He makes good jokes sometimes. Never a boring moment.

I loved the course. Good prof. It taught me how to make things I never would have thought I could make. Daniel is supportive and nice, and flexible if you talk to him about doing something outside or beyond the project.
An amazing teacher, learned a lot, classes were fun and interactive, one of my favorite teachers by far.

Very kind man. You have to be a little wacky to get a good grade in his course, but that's like all the art courses. Very laid back and easy to talk to. Unclear about project guidelines, but again, usual with art classes.
